/*  LU factorization of a sparse matrix in COO format.
    The matrix is stored in CSR(Compressed Sparse Row) form internally to avoid
    creating a full NxN dense matrix.  The algorithm is a straight‑forward
    Doolittle LU without partial pivoting, matching the reference implementation
    behaviour exactly.  A small amount of vectorised work and OpenMP parallelism
    are used to accelerate the execute loop.  */
void luFactorize(std::vector<COOElement> const& A,
